              "semantic_type": "TextAtom",
              "is_public": true,
              "text": "## Introduction\nAfter you’ve defined a problem statement that matters, building an analysis roadmap helps you stay efficient with your time. An analysis roadmap consists of two key elements: (1) an issue tree and (2) a ghost deck. \n\nAn issue tree that comprises of set of exhaustive hypotheses that help break down a problem statement into its component parts. Once you’ve built out an effective issue tree and planned your analyses, your ready to move onto building a ghost deck. A ghost deck is a skeleton deck that includes an executive summary template, an overview of your analyses, “blank” analyses, and recommendation/next step template.\n",
              "instructor_notes": ""
            }
          ]
        },
