              "title": "commonly asked questions",
              "semantic_type": "TextAtom",
              "is_public": true,
              "text": "#### Question: Should hypotheses be stated as statements or questions? Does it matter?\n\nAnswer: Hypotheses can be stated both as statements and questions. Either way, they need to be supported by data and evidence.\n\nIt is important to remember that hypothesis is based on early exploratory analysis, and not an opinion. Here is a [blog](http://workingwithmckinsey.blogspot.com/2014/02/Being-Hypothesis-Driven.html) that talks about specifying hypothesis clearly.",
