            {
              "id": 847758,
              "key": "cf455468-3088-4d5a-a8e2-865a66ba5c3d",
              "title": "List_ what is effective ghost deck",
              "semantic_type": "TextAtom",
              "is_public": true,
              "text": "## Elements of an effective ghost deck:\n\n### The Synthesis:\n● Is also known as an executive summary<br>\n● Addresses the “so what?” to your analyses<br>\n● Includes a succinct recommendation and proposed next steps<br>\n\n### Logical Train of Thought:<br>\n● Follows clear logic from one analysis to another<br>\n● Includes headings that read by themselves<br>\n\n### Caveats:\n● Includes a call out to the limitations and biases of the analyses, e.g., biases that affect the final recommendation\n\n## Reading on the importance and components of a ghost deck: \n* How to [Apply Ghost Decks](https://medium.com/jong-park/how-to-apply-ghost-aka-shell-and-skeleton-decks-7692a942c802)<br>\n* [What is a Ghost Deck?](http://workingwithmckinsey.blogspot.com/2013/07/McKinsey-presentations-ghost-decks.html)\n",
              "instructor_notes": ""
            }
          ]
        },
